The paper deals with missing data estimation using deep learning and swarm intelligence algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The methodology involves modeling the data distribution and minimizing an error function based on the interrelationship and correlation between features in the dataset, which are also relevant to neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). The use of swarm intelligence algorithms is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with high-dimensional datasets, which is a common problem in data science and statistics (cs.DS).
